            <Placemark>
                <name>01 Dunav Camping Donau Beograd</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-04-08T17:24:29Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - Beograd Camping Donau
Price: 2 x 8,-€/night/person
Campground: next to the Donau river, clean, quiet 
Sanitair: clean (we were the only guests), OK
Electricity: availabe
Wifi: no
Price is OK for a quite night (about 7-10Km away from the highway) and with a hot shower. 
                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>20.355767011642456</longitude>
                    <latitude>44.878202984109521</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        20.355767011642456,44.878202984109521,100.9688                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
            <Placemark>
                <name>02 BC Edrine hills</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-04-10T03:39:55Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - First (wild) camp in Turkey not far from the border. Off the highway in the fields in the middle of nowhere. Quite night exept for some far away factory noise in the early morning. 
                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>26.644321968778968</longitude>
                    <latitude>41.605285964906216</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        26.644321968778968,41.605285964906216,90.185249999999996                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
            <Placemark>
                <name>03 BC hills Keskin</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-04-10T15:03:50Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - Excellent wild camp spot with nice view on hils. Very quite.                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>33.570630960166454</longitude>
                    <latitude>39.683469962328672</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        33.570630960166454,39.683469962328672,1016.7430000000001                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
            <Placemark>
                <name>04 BC Nemrut Daggi</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-04-11T16:04:13Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - Nemrut Daggi is meanwhile a World culture heritage. After a very steep car climb we got into the Nemrut park and were positively surprised that we are allowed to stay for the night within the park. The Nemrut is exceptional at sunrise and sunset. It was still (in April) freezing during the night given the altitude of 2.100 meter. Busses come in the morning with tourist to experience the sunrise. 
                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>38.737300029024482</longitude>
                    <latitude>37.976276027038693</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        38.737300029024482,37.976276027038693,2012.5                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
