            <Placemark>
                <name>08 BC Gabhir Garden Isfahan</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-04-15T07:45:52Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - Used by many overlanders. Parking with fence and police surveillance and public toilets. Small growcery stores accross the street which supply bread, water, an others... Initialy the police did not want us to sleep here. After some discussion we were allowed to park and sleep in front of the police caravan on the parking. 
                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>51.715303966775537</longitude>
                    <latitude>32.640597028657794</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        51.715303966775537,32.640597028657794,1587.8889999999999                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
            <Placemark>
                <name>09 BC Yazd in front of Silkroad Hotel</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-04-17T05:50:53Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - Very recommendable wild camp on public parking in front of the Silk Road hotel. This is the most central wild camp place in Yazd with 100 meter walk to public toilets (which have also soap) which are located left on the street 50 meter in front of the scenic mosque. We were allowed to use the wifi of the Silk Road hotel for free. 
                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>54.369941968470812</longitude>
                    <latitude>31.900920979678631</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        54.369941968470812,31.900920979678631,1214.78                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
