            <Placemark>
                <name>15 BC close to highway to Bukhara</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-04-23T02:31:57Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - Wild camp off the new highway to Bukhara within the dunes. First we tried the other site of the highway direct at the river. However, military visited us and we needed to leave as the border with Turkmenitan is too close. 
                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>61.464622020721436</longitude>
                    <latitude>41.33080679923296</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        61.464622020721436,41.33080679923296,179.72640000000001                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
            <Placemark>
                <name>16 BC parking hotel Asia Bukhara</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-04-23T11:49:47Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - Wild camp on the parking of the hotel Asia Bukhara protected by fence and security guard. Clean toilets, water and wifi available. Asked hotel manager if we could stay. Payed parking guard 2000 Sum (~0,65 Euro). Excellent location direct in front of the old town. 

                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>64.419183963909745</longitude>
                    <latitude>39.77391698397696</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        64.419183963909745,39.77391698397696,280.72120000000001                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
            <Placemark>
                <name>17 BC guesthouse Bahodir Samarquand</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>1970-01-01T00:00:00Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - This great place is well known among Uzbekistan budget travelers. You meet here interesting people from all over the world. Also the location can not be better as everything is in walking distance just behind the Registan. We paid for using shower breakfast/dinner and therefore we could sleep in our cars in front of the guesthouse. The guesthouse did do the mandatory registration for us. 
                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>66.979286670684814</longitude>
                    <latitude>39.656323911622167</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        66.979286670684814,39.656323911622167,0.02                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
