            <Placemark>
                <name>31 BC the Celestial mountains Naryn</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>1970-01-01T00:00:00Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - The Celestial mountains Naryn. A good and convenient place to relax a few days and to get everything washed and cleaned. They have shared toilets and hot showers in rather small compartments which are cleaned every day. They serve a better than expected breakfast and dinner at the basement dining room. All in all a good all rounder and good value but lacked the character of the other homestay places we stayed in. 
Price: 200 Sum (2,60€) /person/night (use of hot shower inlcuded), 200 Sum (2,60 €) /person for breakfast, 350 Sum (4,55€)/person for a good dinner 
Campground: after fence/wall, we did sleep in our car, up to 5-6 cars can park next to the guesthouse
Sanitair: European style toilet, hot shower (old but clean) 
Laundery service: 300 Sumoni (3,90€/machine)
Electricity: we didn't use
Wifi: yes (free)

                </description>       
                <LookAt>
                    <longitude>76.021566716954112</longitude>
                    <latitude>41.429136749356985</latitude>
                    <range>500</range>
                    <tilt>45</tilt>
                    <heading>0</heading>
                </LookAt>
                <Point>
                    <coordinates>
                        76.021566716954112,41.429136749356985,0                        
                    </coordinates>
                </Point>
            </Placemark>
                                                                        
            
            <Placemark>
                <name>32 BC return (snow and broken bridge)</name>                      
                <visibility>1</visibility>            
                <open>0</open>                        
                                                    
                <TimeStamp>
                    <when>2014-05-18T10:31:28Z</when>
                </TimeStamp> 
                                
                <description>
                     - Our plan was to pass the mountains to get to Lake Issyk Kul. This route is really remote and not often used due to snow conditions. We needed to return as both snow and a broken bridge made it impossible to continue. However we were very happy to have experienced this fantastic scenery. 
                </description>       
                <LookAt>
